  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single OpenType variable font axis, including its four-byte tag, name ID, value range, and default value.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` represents the metadata for one axis in an OpenType
variable font, as returned by
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters*> or the
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> property.

Each axis has a four-byte <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Tag> (such as
`wght` for weight or `wdth` for width), a floating-point value range given by
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Min> and
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Max>, and a
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis.Default> value.

This is a value type; no disposal is required.

## Examples

```csharp
var axes = typeface.VariationDesignParameters;
foreach (var axis in axes)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Axis: {axis.Tag}, Range: [{axis.Min}, {axis.Max}], Default: {axis.Default}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
